d that has run into a floor. From 23 June through to 1 July, EUR/GBP traded in a tight range just above 0.8610, before a decisive break lower on 1 July accelerated the move toward the 0.8455 area \u2014 a level that marked the swing low on 15 July. Since that flush, price has recovered modestly, but the recovery has been shallow and laboured. The four identified resistance zones all sit well above current price: the 0.8618 and 0.8610 prior reaction zones are the nearest overhead references, having previously acted as support during the late-June consolidation and now flipped to potential resistance on any attempted recovery. Above those, the 0.8652 and 0.8682 zones represent more substantial prior reaction areas where sellers have shown up repeatedly \u2014 five touches each on the daily chart, lending them considerable structural weight.\n\nThe intraday picture on the H1 reinforces the neutral desk read. Yesterday afternoon saw a steady grind higher from around 0.8493, with price climbing through the European close and into the Asian session, reaching a session high of 0.8539 around the 23:00 candle. Since that point, however, the move has entirely stalled. The last twelve hours of H1 data show price coiling in an exceptionally tight range between approximately 0.8519 and 0.8527, with candle bodies barely a pip wide in places. This is classic pre-resolution compression \u2014 the market is waiting for a catalyst.\n\nThe calendar is empty today, which is a notable feature in itself. With no scheduled data releases or central bank commentary flagged, the absence of event risk means any volatility that does emerge is more likely to be technically or flow-driven rather than fundamental. Thin conditions can occasionally produce exaggerated moves through key levels, so the proximity of the 0.8618 resistance cluster warrants attention should sterling weaken on any cross-market development.\n\nWhat would change the read? A sustained daily close back above the 0.8618 prior reaction zone would begin to challenge the bearish structural narrative and open a conversation about the 0.8652 cluster. Conversely, a clean break below the 15 July swing low around 0.8454 would suggest the recovery attempt has failed entirely and that the broader downtrend remains the dominant force. Until either of those scenarios plays out, the desk holds a neutral stance, treating the current range as unresolved.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}